<li><cite id="Randall" class="citation book"><a href="/wiki/Willard_Sterne_Randall" title="Willard Sterne Randall">Randall, Willard Sterne</a> (1990). <i>Benedict Arnold: Patriot and Traitor</i>. William Morrow and Inc. <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1-55710-034-9" title="Special:BookSources/1-55710-034-9">1-55710-034-9</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABenedict+Arnold&amp;rft.aufirst=Willard+Sterne&amp;rft.aulast=Randall&amp;rft.btitle=Benedict+Arnold%3A+Patriot+and+Traitor&amp;rft.date=1990&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.isbn=1-55710-034-9&amp;rft.pub=William+Morrow+and+Inc&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> This book is a comprehensive biography, and goes into great detail about Arnold's part in military operations in Quebec, as well as much of the behind-the-scenes political and military wrangling and infighting that occurred prior to his defection. It also includes detailed accounts of his negotiations with André and Clinton.</li>
