<li>Thompson, Keith. <i>Scoundrel! The Secret Memoirs of General James Wilkinson</i> (2012) <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-935254-66-9" title="Special:BookSources/978-1-935254-66-9">978-1-935254-66-9</a> A novel written from the viewpoint of James Wilkinson, who was Arnold's aide in Canada in 1776. Though a work of fiction, the last few weeks of Arnold's campaign in Canada is covered with surprising accuracy and insight.</li>
<li><cite class="citation book"><a href="/wiki/Charles_Burr_Todd" title="Charles Burr Todd">Todd, Charles Burr</a> (1903). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/?id=C8R2AAAAMAAJ&amp;dq=Benedict%20Arnold%20Todd&amp;pg=PP7"><i>The Real Benedict Arnold</i></a>. New York: A.S. Barnes. <a href="/wiki/OCLC" title="OCLC">OCLC</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.worldcat.org/oclc/1838934">1838934</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABenedict+Arnold&amp;rft.aufirst=Charles+Burr&amp;rft.aulast=Todd&amp;rft.btitle=The+Real+Benedict+Arnold&amp;rft.date=1903&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=A.S.+Barnes&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2F%3Fid%3DC8R2AAAAMAAJ%26dq%3DBenedict%2520Arnold%2520Todd%26pg%3DPP7&amp;rft_id=info%3Aoclcnum%2F1838934&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
